FT  27 JAN 93 / International Company News: Daf delays recovery plan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RONALD VAN DE KROL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   EINDHOVEN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
TALKS aimed at devising a long-awaited recovery plan for Daf, the
loss-making Dutch truck maker, ended inconclusively last night but efforts
were due to be resumed today, writes Ronald van de Krol in Eindhoven.
Daf was due to unveil a recovery programme yesterday afternoon but its plans
were thrown into disarray by hitches between the four parties involved -
Daf, its bankers, the Dutch state and Belgium's Flemish regional government.
The recovery plan is forecast to include fresh financing for the company.
