<HEADLINE>
FT  27 JAN 93 / UK Company News: Reckitt buys Mantovani
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HAIG SIMONIAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Reckitt &amp; Colman, the food, pharmaceuticals and personal hygiene group, is
buying the Mantovani division of the Star foods company in Italy, writes
Haig Simonian.
Mantovani, a well known brand in Italy, comprises the bulk of Star's soaps
and personal care products activities, with annual sales of about L50bn
(Pounds 22m).
No price for the transaction has been disclosed.
The deal will raise Reckitt's sales in Italy, which stand at L100bn at
present, by about 50 per cent. It will also give it its first manufacturing
presence in the country.
Star, which is 55 per cent owned by the Italian Fossati family, has been
moving back to its core food activities.
The other shareholders are BSN, the French foods group, and Ifil, the
Agnelli family's quoted investment vehicle. Group sales amounted to L708bn
last year with net earnings of L29.3bn.
</TEXT>
