appointments in March.
George is in for a hard time. The Treasury committee report is expected
unanimously to criticise the Bank of England in its handling of BCCI.
But at least Radice still has a soft spot for Pennant-Rea. 'He was very much
a child of the 1960s, you know,' says he whimsically.
