<HEADLINE>
FT  27 JAN 93 / People: Non-executive director for The Economist
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Professor George Bain (right), the principal of London Business School, has
been appointed a non-executive director of The Economist Newspaper Ltd,
publisher of one of the world's most influential business weeklies. He is
the first non-executive to join the board since Sir Evelyn de Rothschild
retired in July.
Bain, 53, joins the board just as the 149-year-old magazine begins its
search for a new editor to replace Rupert Pennant-Rea who has been appointed
deputy governor of The Bank of England. The Economist is half-owned by the
Financial Times.
