FT  27 JAN 93 / Parliament and Politics: Aid for special projects suspended
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Tim Sainsbury, the industry minister, announced in the Commons last night
that aid provided for special projects under the Industrial Development Act
would be suspended until April 1995.
Labour MPs accused him of 'sneaking through' the announcement during a
debate on the provision of up to Pounds 20m to enable the Swedish
paper-making company SCA to invest in a newspaper recy-cling plant at
Aylesford, Kent.
Mr Sainsbury said it was intended to suspend the operation of the assistance
for special projects facility from the end of February.
MPs approved an order authorising sums exceeding Pounds 10m but not Pounds
20m towards the cost of installing new machinery and refurbishing existing
machinery to manufacture newsprint from recycled fibre at Aylesford.
