FT  27 JAN 93 / Defence agency to be trading fund
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE DEFENCE Research Agency, which runs the four armed forces research
establishments, is to become a trading concern from April 1.
The DRA is the ninth government executive agency to become a trading fund,
required to manage its finances much more like a commercial company. It will
face increasing competition for the research work it carries out for the
Defence Ministry.
An order laid before parliament last week by Mr Malcolm Rifkind, the defence
secretary, capitalises the agency at Pounds 328m. It will have turnover of
more than Pounds 800m.
