FT  27 JAN 93 / The Base Rate Cut: Base rate cut could lead to extra car
sales this year
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GRIFFITHS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
YESTERDAY's base rate cut should lead to 50,000 extra car sales this year
provided the chancellor does not introduce a tax-raising Budget in March,
the Retail Motor Industry Federation said last night, John Griffiths writes.
The rate cut came less than 24 hours after the federation, which represents
12,000 retail motor trade businesses, unveiled a pre-Budget submission
warning that without lower interest rates a forecast 5 per cent recovery in
new car sales to 1.67m this year could peter out.
The reduction was also given a cautious welcome by the Society of Motor
Manufacturers and Traders whose chief executive, former Tory MP Sir Hal
Miller, said that 'through his actions, the chancellor seems to be on our
side'.
