FT  26 JAN 93 / The Economy: Unions to challenge 1.5% pay ceiling
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA WOOD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PUBLIC SECTOR unions representing nearly 1m council manual workers yesterday
issued a challenge to the government's 1.5 per cent pay rise ceiling, Lisa
Wood writes.
Mr Roger Poole, general-secretary of Nupe, the public services union, said a
meeting of local government manual unions yesterday had decided that this
year's pay claim 'will be prepared without regard to the limit'.
A similar message will be delivered today by leaders of 750,000 local
government white-collar workers. Nalgo representatives will tell employers
that the limit is 'unfair and unjustifiable'.
The Local Government Management Board, which negotiates on behalf of
councils, said yesterday that this year's government grant meant some local
authorities could not afford 1.5 per cent.
The board said: 'Whatever union leaders might be saying at this early stage,
the fact is that if local authorities agree to more than they can afford it
is the staff and the local communities who end up paying with reduced
services and more job losses.'
