<HEADLINE>
FT  26 JAN 93 / Labour warns on R&amp;D spending
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE UK will suffer because of the sharp fall in spending on research and
development in recent years, Mr Robin Cook, the shadow trade and industry
secretary, warned yesterday.
Government figures for 1991 showed that in that year alone the UK had lost
10 per cent of its spending and of its workforce in R&amp;D, he said, even
before the worst of the recession. The government's own contribution had
fallen by 22 per cent.
Mr Cook warned that unless ministers acted to increase R&amp;D 'Britain will not
be the world's workshop but merely its assembly line'.
