<HEADLINE>
FT  26 JAN 93 / World Trade News: GEC Alsthom in Mexican deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GEC Alsthom, the Anglo-French power engineering group, has won a Pounds 400m
turnkey contract to build a 2 x 350MW oil-fired power station near Tuxpan in
Veracruz state, Mexico, Andrew Baxter reports.
GEC Alsthom was selected by the Mexican Federal Electricity Commission for
the job, and is project leader in a consortium which includes two of its
subsidiaries.
