swap
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SANTA FE PACIFIC, the US railroad and minerals group, and Hanson, the
UK-based conglomerate, last night formally signed an agreement swapping
major mineral assets, writes Nikki Tait in New York.
The deal was first revealed two weeks ago and involves assets worth around
Dollars 500m on each side.
Under the agreement, Hanson is acquiring virtually all of Santa Fe's coal
assets, including the Lee Ranch Coal Mine and undeveloped coal reserves
located mainly in New Mexico. Santa Fe is taking over certain gold assets
belonging to Hanson's Gold Fields Mining Company.
